      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTORLEFTALONE (4) resumes after showing promise in a brief juvenile campaign, winning at Bathurst on debut before tackling the Shakamaker Classic at Melton when last seen on October. Likely to have developed further with maturity and was readied with a trial. Looks well placed for a winning return. FLYING MAJOR ART NZ (3) is stepping out for the first time. By Art Major and hails from the Michael Stanley stable. Showed ability in winning a trial at this circuit and distance and should enjoy an economical run from this draw so expecting a good start to his career. WHERES MY REASON (7) hasn't raced since tackling a Group 1 here four-and-a-half months ago. Recorded a series of placings prior and goes well fresh with a win and a placing in two attempts. EYE CAN EAR AMOUR (5) was readied with a nice trial and won her lone fresh attempt so keep safe.",
